Phase 5 — Order placement
Service: order-service · PostgreSQL `orders` db, calling identity-service
and catalog-service over gRPC

First phase requiring the two cross-service gRPC calls from
proto/identity-proto and proto/catalog-proto (GetUser, GetProduct/
ReserveStock). This is the riskiest integration point in the whole system
— everything before this phase was a single service; this is the first
place a request's success depends on two other services being correct and
reachable. Isolated into its own phase for exactly that reason.

Scenarios covered: 16, 17, 18, 19, 20.

---

## POST /api/orders

Scenario 16 (happy path), 17 (insufficient stock), 18 (idempotent retry).

Server-side flow per request (see ARCHITECTURE.md §4 and
Archive/Development/Database §2.3/§3):
1. gRPC IdentityService.GetUser(customerId from the JWT claim) — confirm
   the account exists and is Active (ORD-001). Deactivated -> reject
   before touching catalog or orders at all.
2. For each line item, gRPC CatalogService.GetProduct then ReserveStock —
   atomic per product, all-or-nothing across the whole order (ORD-007). If
   any reservation fails, any already-succeeded reservations for this same
   request must be released again (compensating action) — no partial
   deduction survives a rejected order.
3. Only after every reservation succeeds: insert the orders + order_items
   rows in Postgres, capturing name/price at this moment (ORD-005),
   status PLACED.
4. Publish `order.placed` to RabbitMQ after the Postgres commit (Phase 7
   picks this up).

Request:
```json
POST /api/orders
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for Alice>
Idempotency-Key: idem-alice-checkout-0001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    { "productId": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001", "quantity": 2 },
    { "productId": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003", "quantity": 1 }
  ]
}
```

Response — 201 Created (ORD-006: totalAmount = 89.99*2 + 129.00*1 = 308.98):
```json
{
  "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
  "customerId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-4aaa-8aaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "status": "PLACED",
  "totalAmount": "308.98",
  "items": [
    { "productId": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001", "productName": "Trail Runner 2.0", "unitPrice": "89.99", "quantity": 2, "lineTotal": "179.98" },
    { "productId": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003", "productName": "Wireless Earbuds Pro", "unitPrice": "129.00", "quantity": 1, "lineTotal": "129.00" }
  ],
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T14:00:00Z"
}
```

Response — 409 Conflict (scenario 17, ORD-007/GEN-001 — Bilal tries to buy
5 of a zero-stock product; the whole request is rejected, nothing else in
the request is touched even if other line items had stock):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "INSUFFICIENT_STOCK",
    "message": "One or more items could not be reserved in the requested quantity.",
    "details": [
      { "productId": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002", "requested": 5, "available": 0 }
    ]
  }
}
```

Response — 201 Created, same body as the original (scenario 18, ORD-009 —
retrying with the same Idempotency-Key header returns the already-created
order instead of creating a second one; no new gRPC reservation calls are
made on the retry):
```json
{
  "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
  "customerId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-4aaa-8aaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "status": "PLACED",
  "totalAmount": "308.98",
  "items": [ "...same as above, unchanged..." ],
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T14:00:00Z"
}
```

Response — 401/403 (ORD-001 — no guest checkout, and a Deactivated
customer cannot place new orders; same identical-error posture as ACC-005
applies here too, so this doesn't leak *which* account-state problem it
was beyond "not eligible"):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "NOT_ELIGIBLE_TO_ORDER",
    "message": "This account cannot place an order."
  }
}
```

